rbindet eine umfassende Darstellung der wesentlichen Aspekte antiker Rhetorik mit vertiefenden Einzelanalysen und möchte zugleich zur Einführung dienen und für das Fachpublikum von Interesse sein.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aRhetoric, Ancient. 4aAntike Rhetorik. 4aKommunikation. 4aLiterarische Rhetorik. 4aPersuasion. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Rhetoric.2bisacsh  aClassical Rhetoric.  aCommunication.  aLiterary Rhetoric.  aPersuasion.1 aAsper, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaier, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeer, Beate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBreuer, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurkard, Thorsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErler, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErler, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFron, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFögen, Thorsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeßler, Jan Erik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKalverkämper, Hartwig, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKirchner, Roderich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoch, Nadia J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeidl, Christoph G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeonhardt, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aManuwald, Gesine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRapp, Christof, ec